Casting Fury percentage chance to activate:<br>
<br>
I: 2%<br>
II: 4%<br>
III: 7%<br>
<br>
From experience (not mine)<br>
Casting Fury damage bonus (constant?):<br>
<br>
I: +33%<br>
II: +66%<br>
III: +100%<br>
<br>
So, the total change in damage output from the 3 skills is:<br>
<br>
I: .02 x .33 = .006 or +0.6% (pathetic)<br>
II: .04 x .66 = .026 or + 2.6% (marginal)<br>
III: .07 x 1.00 = .07 or +7.0% (decent)<br>
<br>
Keep in mind that this bonus to efficiency only applies to DD and is inconstant, unpredictable, and liable to generate unwanted aggro.<br>
<br>
Now, what is our sitting meditation rate?  I'll admit that I have no idea.  Let's base our calculations around the number 25.  This is probably wrong but not too wrong <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Mental Clarity<br>
<br>
I: +1 regen, 1/25 = .04 = 4.0% increase<br>
II: +2 regen, 2/25 = .08 = 8.0% increase<br>
III +3 regen, 3/25 = .12 = 12% increase<br>
<br>
If regen is 30, 3.3%,6.6%,9.9%<br>
If regen is 20, 5%, 10%, 15%<br>
<br>
Note: the bonus to efficiency of Mental Clarity applies to all spells cast.<br>
<br>
The point I guess is that although Casting Fury looks flashy and cool, Mental Clarity is much better.  In fact, it is more efficient to put 3 points into Mental Clarity than 2 in MC and 2 in CF (both of which options have the same total point cost).  <br>
<br>
I have made a few assumptions in this post:<br>
<br>
1. CF bonus damage is a constant.  If this is false, CF is much worse than I have described.<br>
2. The percentage chance of CF activating is 2%, 4%, and 7% respectively at levels I, II, and III.  These are the numbers Verant has provided.  However, they have been known to be wrong.<br>
3.  Standard mana regen rate at 60 (sitting) is somewhere between 20 and 30.  If it higher, the numbers for MC go down.  If lower, they go up.<br>
<br>
Dumb Math:<br>
<br>
For the sake of simplicity, I have given CF a slight edge in the calculations above.  To calculate the true bonus given my MC, one should use the following formula:<br>
<br>
( (percentage time standing) * (mana regen standing/MC bonus) ) + ( (percentage time medding) * (mana regen sitting/MC bonus) )<br>
<br>
